theorem.statement:
\[\text{A function } T: \mathbf{V} \to \mathbf{W} \text{ is a linear transformation if it satisfies the following conditions:}\]
      \begin{align*}
        &T(\mathbf{u} + \mathbf{v}) = T(\mathbf{u}) + T(\mathbf{v}), \\
        &T(c\mathbf{u}) = cT(\mathbf{u})
      \end{align*}
